Questions after the accident: Are stewards on the bus unlawful?
The law does not know them, in a long-distance coach, walking around is not allowed
In connection with the tragic accident of a bus of the company Student Agency near the Italian Padua, the question arises whether stewards and travelers are allowed to walk back and forth while driving on the bus.
"If we wanted to strictly and formally comply with the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," said the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident, which killed a twenty-two-year-old stewardess last week, was likely caused by the truck's driver crossing the bus.
The young woman sat next to the driver at that moment to all the misfortune, in the least safe place in the car, although she had two more places at her disposal.
However, a bus can also have an accident or brake sharply at the moment when the steward carries out coffee or newspapers.
It also plays a role whether the bus is also equipped with standing places according to the vehicle certificate.
If this is not provided for in the bus, the travelers must sit.
Student Agency's long-distance coaches have no standing places; which the company's director, Radim Jančura, confirmed to Aktuálně.cz.
“We discussed this with the ministry, and this did not first agree to the movement of travellers.
Later, this was taken back, and we have reached a consensus that travelers are allowed to go to the toilet while driving when they have their seat," he shared his point of view.
The law knows no steward
“There is no clear legal interpretation for the role of a steward – no legislation describes this role.
However, there is also no legislation prohibiting the carrier from providing services.
The law on road traffic only knows the term vehicle attendant; however, its rights and obligations do not define it," adds the spokesman for the Ministry Hanzelka clearly.
The Director of the Road Vehicles Department of the Ministry of Transport Josef Pokorný, on the other hand, thinks that the law subsequently covers this problem.
“It depends on whether the bus also has standing places in the product approval.
That's all," he insists.
Buses are divided into city buses, where there are standing places and the maximum speed is limited, local buses with standing places and a higher permitted speed and long-distance coaches without standing places with the highest permissible speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on an airplane, says the professional
The BESIP specialist for road safety Jaroslav Hořín sees no fundamental problem in the movement of stewards on board a bus.
“With a smooth driving style, not many dangers threaten, the situation is comparable to the service on board an aircraft.
Again, it is not certain when turbulence will come, and the stewardess can hit his head."
“However, if a bus brakes sharply, then of course the laws of physics also apply.
Just like on a city bus or on a tram.
The safety of the stewards must be cleared by the carrier through internal regulations," he says, and also thinks that this problem is not fully solved from the point of view of the law.
Jančura is ready to cancel the services
Student Agency is the only bus company to offer services from stewards.
The company employs about two hundred people in this function.
The director does not consider their profession to be risky even after the accident.
“But as soon as I get the impression that the profession of steward is high-risk, I will delete it.
Coffee and newspapers can be obtained by travellers when boarding.
That would also reduce costs," he said.
As an interest in safety, the director of Asiana Alexei Litvin justifies the lack of stewards on his buses. However, his company operates only a fraction of lines compared to Student Agency.
“We don’t have stewardesses, we’ve been fighting back from the beginning.
Sooner or later, this ends with some fatal accident," he had said not quite a year ago for Týden.cz.
This was an incredible tragedy
In the accident of a regular-service bus to Naples, a young stewardess from the Pilsen region had died, who had worked for the company for two years.
The Slovenian truck had probably turned off the strip without blinking and had blocked the bus from driving.
The driver of the bus tried to dodge through a sharp maneuver, but collided with the right front with the truck.
Jančura denies that the two seats for the stewards had been sold.
“These places cannot be reserved on long-distance connections, they are blocked.”
Company wants to sue truck drivers.
With compensation for the young woman's family, the agency will not wait for the court ruling, but she also expects financial damages from the culprit.
A change in the law?
Not in sight
A more precise settlement of the movement of stewards on board a bus could bring a legal regulation that a thirty-member team of experts from the Ministry of Transport has been working on for over a year.
“However, this has not yet reached a concrete conclusion.
Buses are also not necessarily on the agenda, rather the points system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of mobile phones when driving," according to expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of the stewards as something that could significantly jeopardize the safety of the travelers," said Hanzelka, with the control of the safety of the buses in the competence of the police and the occupational health and safety authorities.
